The National Association of Community Health Practitioners of Nigeria (NACHPN) has commenced nationwide sensitisation campaign against COVID-19 in rural areas to prevent the outbreak of corona virus at the grassroots. The National Publicity Secretary of the association, Mr Elijah Alkali-Zakwoyi, made this known in Abuja while speaking with journalists on Community Health Practitioners’ strategies of safeguarding rural dwellers from the scourge of coronavirus. Alkali-Zakwoyi said the sensitization campaign is centred on the practice of hand washing, respiratory hygiene, surfaces hygiene at home, and practice of social distancing “At this period of COVID-19, it is very important for all Nigerians most especially rural dwellers to regularly wash their hands with clean running water and soap, in between hands rub hand sanitizer, cough into a tissue paper and dispose properly and sneeze into their elbow,” he said. According to him, the sensitization campaign would continue until coronavirus is finally eradicated in Nigeria. He therefore advised all Nigerians most especially those at the grassroots to obey government’s directives on COVID-19 and imbibe good hygiene and clean sanitary and environmental conditions. Alkali-Zakwoyi also advised them to report anyone with high temperature, ceaseless coughing, sneezing and sore throat, to the nearer health facility or call NCDC free toll numbers.